TITLE: Biden, in newly released Nov. 4 video, says Iran nuclear deal 'dead'
SUMMARY: President Biden called the Iran nuclear deal "dead" in conversation with a group of activists on Nov. 4, according to newly surfaced footage on Twitter.

TITLE: Southern border in limbo as Title 42 hangs in balance after temporary Supreme Court stay
SUMMARY: Officials and migrans along the southern border are left in limbo after the Supreme Court put a temporary stay on the ending of the Title 42 public health order.

TITLE: ICE plans to release illegal immigrants in Tennessee to await court proceedings, governor says
SUMMARY: Tennessee Republican Gov. Bill Lee tells Fox News Digital that ICE plans to “release single adult detainees” into the Volunteer State as they await court proceedings.

TITLE: GOP scores win in $1.7T budget deal by cutting IRS funding
SUMMARY: Senate Republicans forced Democrats and the White House to cut more than $275 million from the IRS during negotiations over President Biden's $1.7 trillion budget.

TITLE: Top Dem and GOP lawmakers sound off on SCOTUS blocking Biden's immigration moves: 'Nightmare at our border'
SUMMARY: Democrat and GOP politicians say Title 42, a COVID-era policy implemented under Trump to expel illegal immigrants, stops a nightmarish border situation from worsening

TITLE: Planned Parenthood in Kansas announces telemedicine abortions
SUMMARY: Medication abortions through telemedicine are seen as a small step toward potentially much broader access in a Kansas, a state that has become a destination for the procedure.

TITLE: Cartels flooding the border with fentanyl powder and pills, US attorney says as Title 42 policy end looms
SUMMARY: U.S. Attorney Randy Grossman told Fox News Digital his office is working on prosecutions of drug traffickers and cartel drug dealers, along with fentanyl prevention campaigns.

TITLE: ‘Gender-affirming’ care, services part of Biden admin’s strategy to help homeless people
SUMMARY: The White House released a homelessness plan Monday that will instruct local emergency shelters how to provide "gender-affirming care" and harm reduction services.

TITLE: Border Patrol tracks down Honduran drug traffickers on Texas border, one suspect just 14 years old
SUMMARY: US border authorities have detained a group of four Hondurans attempting to cross into Texas through Mexico, also discovering a stash of fentanyl and marijuana.

TITLE: Biden Cabinet member's daughter lobbying Congress on issue her mom has final say on: 'Conflict of interest'
SUMMARY: Interior Secretary Deb Haaland's daughter Somah Haaland lobbied federal lawmakers last week to curb fossil fuel drilling on federal lands, an issue the Interior Department oversees.

TITLE: Electoral Count Act reforms included within Biden's $1.7 trillion bipartisan budget deal
SUMMARY: Lawmakers have tied legislation rewriting the Electoral Count Act to President Biden's $1.7 trillion budget in hopes of averting another January 6 assault on the U.S. Capitol.

TITLE: Jeffries expected to name DelBene as new DCCC head: report
SUMMARY: Rep. Hakeem Jeffries, new House Democratic leader, is expected to nominate Rep. Suzan DelBene to be the next chair off the Democratic Congressional Campaign Committee.

TITLE: Supreme Court leaker of decision overturning Roe still not publicly identified more than 7 months later
SUMMARY: As the new year and new congressional session approach, the Supreme Court has yet to publicly identify who leaked the draft opinion of the case that overturned Roe v. Wade.

TITLE: Racism raises Alzheimer’s risk for non-White Americans, HHS claims in new report
SUMMARY: A new HHS report on how to fight Alzheimer's disease and dementia says racism is a risk factor for non-White Americans, and suggested equity-based solutions.

TITLE: Turning Point Action AmericaFest 2022 straw poll results reveal overwhelming call for new RNC leadership
SUMMARY: A new straw poll revealed participants at Turning Point Action's AmFest want a change in leadership at the RNC and backed Harmeet Dhillion over Ronna McDaniel.

TITLE: Federal judge strikes down California's 'fee-shifting' gun control scheme, which echoed Texas abortion law
SUMMARY: A federal judge said a California law that permits citizens to bring lawsuits against gun makers is unconstitutional, raising questions over a similar Texas abortion law.

TITLE: Democratic Rep. Richard Brown to return to Ohio House next year after recount upholds victory
SUMMARY: Rep. Richard Brown will return to the Ohio House next year after a recount upheld his victory from the November elections. He won the election by 145 votes, which triggered a recount.

TITLE: Republicans push CDC to reinstate defensive gun use data after gun control activists had it removed from site
SUMMARY: Republican lawmakers are pressing the CDC to reinstate data on defensive gun use after removing it from their website. Gun control activists had argued the data was wrong.

TITLE: Twitter Files: RNC demands FEC reopen investigation into censorship of Hunter Biden stories
SUMMARY: The RNC is demanding the Federal Election Commission reopen an investigation into Twitter’s censorship of the Hunter Biden laptop story after the release of the "Twitter Files."

TITLE: Major eco group saw large funding uptick fueled by liberal dark money network: 'Best year ever'
SUMMARY: The League of Conservation Voters, an eco group with strong ties to the Biden administration, reported its highest-ever annual fundraising haul in 2021.
